    Configuration for CounterMetric.

    Fore more details about counters and other metrics please see the documentation of LocalMetricsService.

    See Also:
    LocalMetricsServiceFactory.withMetric(MetricConfigBase), LocalMetricsService.register(CounterConfig)

      • setAutoReset

        public void setAutoReset(boolean autoReset)
        Sets the flag that controls whether this counter should be automatically reset to 0 or should keep its value across refresh intervals.

        Default value of this parameter is false.

        Note: even if this flag is set to true it is still possible to track total value of a counter by specifying setTotalName(String).

        Parameters:
        autoReset - true if this counter should be automatically reset to 0.

      • getTotalName

      • setTotalName

        public void setTotalName(String totalName)
        Sets the name of a metric that will hold the total value of this counter. Can contain only alpha-numeric characters and non-repeatable dots/hyphens.

        This parameter is optional. If specified then an additional metric of that name will be registered within the LocalMetricsService and will hold the total value aggregated during the whole history of this counter.

        Note: In most cases this parameter makes sense only if setAutoReset(boolean) is set to true.

        Parameters:
        totalName - Name of a metric that will hols the total value of this counter (can contain only alpha-numeric characters and non-repeatable dots/hyphens).
